{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/roundup-mtl/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Multitask learning is the learning of multiple (related) tasks <em>simultaneously</em> using a set or subset of <em>shared parameters</em>. By sharing structure across multiple tasks, the hope is to produce more </p>\n<ul>\n<li>general (shared knowledge) representations </li>\n<li>data efficent learning  </li>\n<li>efficient inference due to common representation </li>\n<li>reduced number of parameters</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/marl/audiosetdl\">https://github.com/marl/audiosetdl</a></p>\n<p>A common approach is to optimize a proxy objective that minimizes a weighted linear combination of per-task losses. This only works when tasks do not compete. </p>\n<p>Multitask learning as multiobjective optimization\n<a href=\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/1810.04650.pdf\">https://arxiv.org/pdf/1810.04650.pdf</a></p>\n<p>Gradient surgery for Multitask Learning</p>","excerpt":"Multitask learning is the learning of multiple (related) tasks simultaneously using a set or subset of shared parameters. By sharing structure across multipleâ€¦","frontmatter":{"title":"Roundup of Multitask Learning","date":"2021-04-23T00:00:00.000Z","subject":["ml","roundup","multitask","mtl"],"author":"RSP","featimg":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.0526315789473684,"src":"/static/6b94184bf4dba247eb1687d3f6bd640b/497c6/MTL.png","srcSet":"/static/6b94184bf4dba247eb1687d3f6bd640b/65e33/MTL.png 100w,\n/static/6b94184bf4dba247eb1687d3f6bd640b/69585/MTL.png 200w,\n/static/6b94184bf4dba247eb1687d3f6bd640b/497c6/MTL.png 400w,\n/static/6b94184bf4dba247eb1687d3f6bd640b/2a4de/MTL.png 600w,\n/static/6b94184bf4dba247eb1687d3f6bd640b/6c136/MTL.png 634w","sizes":"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/roundup-mtl/","readingTime":{"text":"1 min read"}}},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"JumpML"}}},"pageContext":{"s